### The Distribution Flywheel (Your Weekly SOP)

A system is only as good as its execution schedule. Do not deviate from this timeline.

* **Thursday (The Inbound Swarm):** Post the Twitter/X hook generated in Step 3. *Do not link the newsletter in the main post.* Link it in the first comment.
* **Friday (The Targeted Strike):** Spend 15 minutes on Reddit (`r/ChatGPT`, `r/PromptEngineering`, etc.). Find one person struggling with the "High-Concept" problem you just wrote about. Reply with your exact "Accurate Mechanism" and "Fix." Add: *"I wrote a whole teardown on this for my systems newsletter, Day One Output."*
* **Saturday (The Hub Drop):** Send the newsletter.
* **Sunday (The Reply Loop):** DM or reply to every single person who liked or commented on your Thursday post: *"Hey, just dropped the full system on [High-Concept Name] in the newsletter. Here's the link."*

**Why this is un-copyable:** If a random creator steals your prompts, the AI will ask them for their specific, visceral "Ghost" and "Bleed". If they don't have a real business, real debt, or real code breaking, the AI will spit out generic fluff. Your constraints are your moat.

